15th anniversary of Ocean Fire with Ryuichi Sakamoto @skmtgram 🌊🔥  The project began with an improvised session in Sakamoto's New York studio, which we later edited and mixed into sections. Meeting Sakamoto in person that first time was unforgettable. We immediately delved into a conversation about noise and harmony over tea before diving into the music. As we listened and created without a thought, time seemed to disappear.
 The process felt like exploring the depths of the ocean: beautiful yet intense, and unknown. This feeling inspired us to explore themes of the ocean and perceived dissonance. The sound of the music, coupled with growing concerns about ocean acidification, led us to choose the title "Ocean Fire." 
Grateful to our friend Taylor Deupree @taylor12k for the stunning cover art, and for releasing the album on his label @12k_label. Ocean Fire was also released by Commmons/Avex in Japan.

To everyone who has listened, thank you!  #willitssakamoto #ryuichisakamoto #christopherwillits #12k #avex #oceanfire

Love you Sakamoto. I learned so much from you and through our music. 🙏🏻❤️

The sound continues, we are listening ♾

#ryuichisakamoto #love

During a studio session for Ancient Future, Ryuichi and I started to come up with titles for each of the pieces.

He said “This one is very mysterious, we should call it I Don’t Want to Understand… because everything we can’t understand!” as he let out that big Sakamoto laugh. We started crying we were laughing so hard. 😂

We can’t “understand” but we can know how we feel. We can make the music, express the grace, and mystery, for us to listen, surrender and be present together. 🙏🏻

Death, I don’t want to understand. ❤️

@skmtgram 
#ryuichisakamoto ♾

My album Sunset is now 4 years old. 🙏🏻 Thank you for listening with me.

Begin the music 15mins before the sun sets. Listen at home or at your favorite sunset spot with headphones. 🌅

Thanks to @ghostly for releasing this music. Thanks to @snowghostmusic for recording this with me and @ryan__kleeman for always backing up my ears, and thanks to @mentamoto for the creativity on the cover art. + always @envelopsound 🙏🏻

“Christopher Willits presents his latest piece, Sunset, with simple instructions: "Begin the music 15 minutes before the sun sets." 

The five compositions move from warm to cool designed as a soundtrack to embrace the day's end; a collective letting go. 

As with 2017's opus Horizon, the first-ever spatial audio release on Ghostly International, Sunset is produced to listen from within. Using the cutting-edge immersive audio venues and tools of his nonprofit, Envelop, Willits projects a path for the future of electronic music. 

“When I was 13, I understood that my life’s path was to make music in the service of love, peace, and spiritual healing. Music is a medicine that allows us to feel, listen and surrender to the present moment. The compositions I create move through my imagination, heart, and hands, like guitar through a speaker, and light through a lens. I am continuously learning and evolving with the process; a practice of letting go of all that I create, as it creates me.” 

#sunset #ambient #ambientmusic #ghostly #guitar #immersiveaudio #spatialaudio

New remix is out today! This is my reinterpretation of Slán, from East Forest and Peter Broderick’s album Burren.

This is all guitar and synth woven into piano stems from Slán.

Remixes are always so fun, it’s like witnessing a puzzle fall into place. I always want to respect the original piece, yet make it my own. That happens through listening and showing up into the sound; feeling and exploring where it all needs to go. The remix becomes a collaboration that pushes me in new directions. It’s always a cool time to touch new sounds and play with the process. 

Much love to my friends @eastforest and @bropeterick for trusting me with their musical baby. 🙏🏻

Link in bio

Study for Sakamoto (March 2023) is out now, part of this beautiful memorial album for Ryuichi that includes so many friends and artists I love. Proceeds go to his initiative Trees for Sakamoto. 🙏🏻🌲 Link in bio to listen. 

This piece is a line of guitar within textures that Ryuichi and I had used in past albums together. Imagining his piano chords drifting on top. 

Working with Sakamoto was a great honor. Through the music we created together, I learned so much about patience, harmony, and space. Before Ryuichi died, I was writing a few pieces to share with him, planting seeds for new ideas together. “Study for Sakamoto (March 2023)” is one of these ideas. Inspired by our collaborations together, this music is one path we may have explored more. While writing this music, I imagined Sakamoto smiling. I’m grateful to share this sound with you.

Musicians involved include:
Alva Noto, Asuna, Bill seaman, Chihei Hatakeyama, Christophe Charles, Christopher Willits, David Cunninghum, David Toop, Federico Durand, Hakobune, urand, Hakobune, Hide Hideki Umezawa, Ian Hawgood, ILLUHA, Kane Ikin, Kazuya Matsumoto, Ken Ikeda, Lawrence English, Marcus Fisher, Marihiko Hara, Miki Yui, Nobuto Suda, Noriko Tsujiko, Otomo Yoshihide, Rie Nakajima, Sawako, Sachiko M, Shuta Hasunuma, Stephan Vitielo, Stijn Huval, SUGAI Ken, Takamasa AOKI, Takashi KOKUBO, Taylor Deupree, Tetuzi Akiyama, The Factors, Tomoko Sauvage, Tomoyoshi Date, Tomotsugu Nakamura, Toshimaru Nakamura, Yui Onodera

Grateful to share this new experience with you! A collaboration with @vesselfloats ✨ 

Lucid Waves is a 48-minute piece of mantra-inspired and gradually modulating moog guitar loops designed for floating. 

A float tank is a warm epsom salt water bath that allows your body to freely float and completely rest. There are many benefits to floating; it allows your nervous system to fully take a break, increases blood flow, and encourages the mind and body to naturally synchronize. It’s very meditative as is, and I created this music to take the experience even deeper. 🙏🏻

I’ve been researching, experimenting, and developing this piece for the last two years with Christian and Vessel. After many months of tests (and trancing myself out!), I feel we’ve created something very special. 

You can listen, in tank, at Vessel Floats in New York. I’ve been floating for the last 10 years and Vessel is, by far, the best experience out there. I’m really excited to share this music and I hope it creates a space of deep relaxation for you. 🛁

Next we will enjoy a live performance by Chihei Hatakeyama, followed by a live performance by Christopher Willits, a tribute to his collaborator and friend, Ryuichi Sakamoto. この魂の癒しとなるイベントは、大禅寺住職の根本一徹紹徹上人の指導による瞑想で調和のとれた夕べのはじまりを迎えます。畠山地平につづきクリストファー・ウィリッツの上演は彼の親愛なる友人である坂本龍一氏へのトリビュート・ライブパフォーマンス。両公演とも、原音に忠実なクアドラフォニック・イマーシブ・サウンドで、深遠なリスニング体験に最適な音の聖域を作り上げることでしょう。

ライブ終了後には、軽食を囲んで談話などのために集まります。この親密なイベントが、みなさんとのつながりや絆を感じるひとときとなることを楽しみにしています。

One year anniversary of Gravity! This music taught me so much; it held a space for me to feel, process, and express everything that was happening in my life, and the world, from 2020-2022. So grateful for everyone listening and feeling their own journey with this music. 🌕

For the anniversary we’re hosting a Gravity listening event at Envelop SF next week! I’ll be there for a Q&A after the music, and I’m really excited to give an early preview of Gravity Remixes, a new compilation on the horizon. 

If you’re not familiar, Envelop SF is the permanent listening space that our nonprofit Envelop @envelopsound operates. 32 speakers immerse you in full-spectrum spatial sound. It’s definitely the best place to listen and feel this music together; I finalized all of the immersive mixes here. I’m so blessed to call it home and lead this amazing team. We’d love to see you, meet you, and listen together. ✨

+ Special thanks to @ghostly for believing in me and this music, and for the years of collaboration. We’re rolling into year 20?! Love you Ghostly crew. ❤️

📸 Cover art for each of the album’s tracks from White Sands. I had two epic roadtrips out there while the album was emerging; driving from SF to KC to see my mom and the fam. 🙏🏻

#envelop #listentogether #sfevents #sanfrancisco #immersivesound #spatialsound #immersiveaudio #spatialaudio #immersivemusic #soundhealing

This one is for Brian. 🙏🏻

Oakland 11/29 w/ Robot Heart 🔥❤️
I’m performing alongside some of my favorite people and artists. So excited to share this night of beautiful music together. Bio link to join. 

Artists:
Christopher Willits - @willits 
Special Guest
Boreta - @boreta 
Adware - @adware1k 
Rozihit Eve - @rozihtmusic 

“Experience an exceptional evening of ambient music at the Robot Heart Residency, featuring the talents of Christopher Willits and some of his closest companions. Immerse yourself in the finest ambient sounds the West Coast has to offer, with the night's conclusion featuring a highly anticipated special guest.  For more than two decades, Willits has been a guiding force in the evolution of deep listening in the Bay Area and beyond. Named “the center cell of a complex Venn diagram in the Bay Area” and “The Picasso of Sound”, Willits has crafted a prolific catalog of exquisite ambient electronic music. Moreover, his nonprofit organization, Envelop, which he both co-founded and directs, serves as a compelling blueprint for the future of immersive listening, while highlighting the profound social and emotional impact of music.  The evening begins with an ethereal set from the talented multi-instrumentalist Roziht Eve, followed by an ambient DJ set from one of SF’s top young producers, and founder of Vitamin 1k, Adware. Boreta will then mesmerize us with brand new in-progress music from his upcoming solo album. Fresh off his tour in Japan, Taiwan, and Thailand, Christopher Willits will perform compositions from his latest albums, “Gravity”, and “Sunset”, along with new improvisations inspired by his friend and collaborator Ryuichi Sakamoto. The energy rises and culminates with a DJ set from a very special guest: a dear friend of Willits and a long-time collaborator with the Robot Heart family”.

#oakland #robotheart #ambient #ambientmusic #electronicmusic #christopherwillits #bayareaevents #oaklandevents

Thankful for all of you! 🙏🏻❤️ Here’s a holiday gift to soak into; my DJ set with Robot Heart from Burning Man. Link in bio. 

Next week we’re bringing the vibes to Oakland at the @robotheartfoundation Residency on 11/29. Would love to see you all with @boreta @adware1k @rozihtmusic and a very special guest DJ that you can probably guess. 🔥🤖 Link in bio for tickets! 

"Friday’s sunrise with Robot Heart, right before the storm. Full of love, resilience, and profound synchronicities, I’m so grateful for this magical moment together.

We all rolled out with the RH bus around 5:30am as the wind was picking up. During the ride out to the deep playa I played sections of Lucid Waves with the heartbeat in the music pulsing with the RH heart.

Once Benji and Justin found our spot, I began the set and a beautiful sparrow spiraled around me and sat by my side. A small window in the clouds let the golden light of the sunrise pour in.

All love for Robot Heart making it happen. Benji, Justin, Ting, the whole crew, thank you. This set was for Geo.”
